========================================================================
                              Editorial
========================================================================
I listen to a lot of the sysop echos, even post in a few of
them. It strikes me, lately, that the fights have become almost
ceremonial in nature.  As if the participants know there has to
be a better way, but have not quite figured out how yet.

It strikes me that relationships should have a reset button.  A
big red one that we could press every once in a while, and start
over.  Without the harsh words.  Without dredging up old history
from a previous, and younger life.

I read the wizard of Oz recently.  Maybe declaring a new
variable actually does create it.  Like magic.

Here is my favourite all time poem by Max.  She called it

Quickie Code:
        push
        push
        push
        POP

P.S.   Please forgive such an unbalanced editorial.
